Iran has put measures in place to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
For information on how to return to the UK from Iran, see Return to the UK
Entry and borders
Some airlines are no longer flying in and out of Iran and many neighbouring countries have closed their borders or started monitoring travellers from Iran.
There may be further measures introduced at short notice. You should comply with any additional screening measures put in place by the authorities, and keep up to date with information from your tour operator, transport or accommodation provider on the impact on any existing travel plans.
Local measures
Some health measures have been put in place in parts of Iran, including temporary closures of schools, universities and public events.
There are reports of imposed travel restrictions in several provinces, including to important tourism and pilgrimage areas.
Further information
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
You can find more information about cases in Iran on the TravelHealthPro country page.
